From 261b881f87c38b9f2d71c2d4ac28b6638f8f86b6 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: developers <developers@tuxbox-neutrino.org>
Date: Sat, 4 Apr 2026 23:48:12 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] fix: do not clean up /newroot after successful daemonize
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The wrapper script had a cleanup trap on EXIT that unmounted and
removed /newroot. When ofgwrite_bin daemonizes via double-fork, the
parent exits with 0, triggering the trap. This destroyed the tmpfs
environment that the daemonized flash process still needs for
pivot_root, mkdir, and binary copies.

Remove the EXIT trap and only clean up on non-zero exit (actual
error). Exit 0 means daemonize succeeded and the flash continues
in the background — /newroot must stay alive.
---
 ofgwrite | 8 +++++++-
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/ofgwrite b/ofgwrite
index 4fb6efd..68e4eb1 100755
--- a/ofgwrite
+++ b/ofgwrite
@@ -11,7 +11,6 @@ cleanup_newroot() {
 }
 
 cleanup_newroot
-trap cleanup_newroot EXIT
 
 mkdir -p /newroot
 mount -t tmpfs tmpfs /newroot
@@ -26,3 +25,10 @@ cp -p /usr/bin/ofgwrite_bin /newroot/
 mount --make-rprivate / >/dev/null 2>&1 || true
 
 /newroot/ofgwrite_bin "$@"
+rc=$?
+
+# Only clean up /newroot if ofgwrite_bin failed. Exit 0 means the process
+# daemonized successfully and the flash is still running in the background.
+if [ "$rc" -ne 0 ]; then
+	cleanup_newroot
+fi
